transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, I was calling to cancel the subscription that you guys have me on.

Speaker 1: Sure. Hold on one second. I'll pull up your profile.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Maceo? Is that how I say your name? Maceo. Maceo.

Speaker 2: Maceo. Can you just confirm your date of birth, please?

Speaker 1: 9-21-74.

Speaker 2: Thank you so much. And how's the medication working out for you?

Speaker 1: It did not.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I think I see the problem. Do you happen to have them on you by chance?

Speaker 1: On me? I mean, they're...

Speaker 2: I have the bottle.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I just want to... Can you take out one pill?

Speaker 2: I just need to know if it says AC imprinted on it.

Speaker 1: It says, yes, AC.

Speaker 2: Yeah, okay. So the pharmacy made an error and just sent you regular generics.

Speaker 1: That's why they're not working.

Speaker 2: Give me a second. I'm going to get you out a replacement

Speaker 1: and then I'm going to tell you how you can confirm you received the replacement.

Speaker 2: And I'm going to send you 100 milligrams instead.

Speaker 1: You could just break them in half if you need to.

Speaker 2: I'm going to send you 25.

Speaker 1: So 20.

Speaker 2: Okay, perfect. All right, that went through.

Speaker 1: Okay, so when you get this new bottle in the mail,

Speaker 2: it's going to say AGB on the bottle, but it's also going to say Greenstone.

Speaker 1: Greenstone is the name of Pfizer's manufacturer in France.

Speaker 2: And then on the pill, the only number imprinted is going to be the number 100 for the milligrams.

Speaker 1: And those are the two ways you can confirm you received the FDA-approved Pfizer-Viagra AGB.

Speaker 2: Because right now, yeah, your pill say AC and on the bottle it says APCO.

Speaker 1: So those are just regular generics.

Speaker 2: And then I'm going to go ahead and pause your refills for six months.

Speaker 1: I'm going to pause it till July 31st.

Speaker 2: That way the pharmacy will be able to send you out that replacement.

Speaker 1: And I'll give you my extension so you can call me back and let me know how the AGB works out for you.

Speaker 2: Give me one second.

Speaker 1: No problem.

Speaker 2: AGB 100.

Speaker 1: Okay, extension.

Speaker 2: Okay, 0020.

Speaker 1: And my name's Michelle.

Speaker 2: One L or two L's?

Speaker 1: Two.

Speaker 2: And then AGB 100 and you said Bluestone?

Speaker 1: Greenstone.

Speaker 2: So Bluestone on the bottle and the only thing imprinted on the pill is going to be the number 100.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Perfect.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: And then July, sorry, June or July?

Speaker 2: July 31st.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: Thank you very much, Michelle.

Speaker 1: No problem.

Speaker 2: Have a great day.

Speaker 1: All right, you too.

Speaker 2: Thanks.

Speaker 1: Bye.
